<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Woodman" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Woodman,</orth> a huntsman: <bibl n="shak. luc 580" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 580</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 28</bibl>. In a wanton sense: <cit><quote>he's a better w. than thou takest him for,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 170</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>